System Architecture for Laundry Connect App

OVERVIEW 
Laundry Connect is an on-demand platform that connects users to laundry women in their area. Users can schedule pickups, track progress, and make secure payments — all in one place.

Architecture Components
1. Frontend
- User-friendly interface for customers and service providers
- Technologies: React.js (Web), React Native (Mobile)
- Key features:
  - User login/signup
  - Order placement and tracking
  - Notifications and order status updates

2. Backend
- Processes all requests and connects the frontend to the database
- Technologies: Node.js with Express.js
- Handles:
  - Authentication and authorization
  - Order management
  - Payment integration
  - Notification and messaging system

3. Database
- Stores users, orders, payments, and provider data
- Technologies: MongoDB
- Collections:
  - Users
  - ServiceProviders
  - Orders
  - Reviews
  - Payments

Data Flow

1. User places an order from the app  
2. Backend verifies and stores the order  
3. Nearby providers are notified  
4. Provider accepts and updates the status  
5. User is notified at every stage  
6. Payment is processed after completion  
7. Order record stored for both users and providers  

System Diagram (Conceptual)

Frontend ↔ Backend ↔ Database  
    ↘ APIs (Payments, Maps, Notifications)
